ANTHRAX - TANZANIA: (KILIMANJARO) HUMAN, BOVINE, SUSPECTED
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 7 Apr 2016
Source: The Citizen [edited]
http://www.thecitizen.co.tz/News/-/1840340/3150016/-/krsdgd/-/index.html


One person has died in Rombo district, Kilimanjaro region, after being [infected] with [_Bacillus anthracis_]. The deceased contracted the infectious disease [anthrax] which is transmitted through contact with meat from an infected animal. 4 other people are receiving treatment at the Huruma Hospital [Rombo district], the designated district medical facility in the area.

Dr Mtumwa Mwako has called on the livestock keepers in the Rombo district to take their animals for vaccination and to avoid consuming meat which has not been certified as safe by veterinary experts.

Symptoms of the anthrax include bleeding profusely, abnormally high temperatures and skin rashes, he said, adding that it may take some time until symptoms became visible. The disease is curable if treated in early stages.

[Byline: Happiness Tesha]

